OL,6,FTheir family home, reduced to ash. But
OL,7,Feven now, Shant holds onto
OL,8,Fperspective: "You didn't really lose
OL,9,Fanything," he recalls a friend telling
OL,10,Fhim.
OL,12,F"The things you lost, they're in your
OL,13,Fheart. They're in your memories...
OL,14,FWe've got one short life to live. So
OL,15,Fwhat are things, really?"
OL,17,FDespite official promises of a swift
OL,18,Frebuild, little has changed. "The
OL,19,Fgrief continues for us and the work
OL,20,Fcontinues for us while the world goes
OL,21,Fon," said Nat.
