OL,6,FLike many others, the Church family
OL,7,Fwere not fully insured ` never
OL,8,Fimagining fire would be the disaster
OL,9,Fto hit them on the coast of the city.
OL,11,FAcross Los Angeles, thousands of homes
OL,12,Fwere either uninsured or underinsured.
OL,14,FEven before the January wildfires,
OL,15,Fseveral insurers had begun pulling out
OL,16,Fof California's high-risk zones,
OL,17,Fciting rising climate volatility and
OL,18,Foutdated regulations. Industry bodies
OL,19,Fsay it is increasingly difficult to
OL,20,Fcover homes in fire-prone areas
OL,21,Faffordably or sustainably.
