OL,3,CAfter the inferno: Can Los Angeles
OL,4,Crise from the ashes?
OL,6,FWith projected losses topping $250
OL,7,Fbillion, rebuilding Los Angeles will
OL,8,Frequire enormous financial investment,
OL,9,Fbut money alone isn't enough. It also
OL,10,Fdepends on labour, especially the
OL,11,Fmigrant workers who, some say, built
OL,12,Fthe city in the first place and are
OL,13,Fnow cleaning it up.
OL,15,FCesar, a volunteer with the National
OL,16,FDay Laborer Organizing Network, is
OL,17,Fhelping detoxify smoke-damaged homes `
OL,18,Fworking slowly, carefully,
OL,19,Fmethodically. "We take four to five
OL,20,Fdays to finish one house. Five
OL,21,Fpeople," he said.
